---
// Contract Language Guide - ChatPRD inspired resource page
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contract Language Guide | Realtor Roof"
  description="Pre-written contract language to protect your buyers when purchasing homes with roof issues."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative py-16 md:py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-200 via-rose-200 to-orange-200"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-tr from-pink-300/40 via-transparent to-rose-300/40"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <a href="/resources" class="inline-flex items-center text-violet-600 hover:text-violet-700 font-semibold mb-8 group">
        <span class="group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform">‚Üê</span>
        <span class="ml-2">Back to Resources</span>
      </a>

      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-100 to-rose-100 border border-pink-200 rounded-full mb-6">
        <span class="text-2xl">üìã</span>
        <span class="text-pink-700 font-semibold text-sm">Essential Resource</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        Contract Language for{' '}
        <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-600 to-rose-600">
          Buyer Protection
        </span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Pre-written contract language you can use to specify Realtor Roof (powered by Maverick Exteriors) for roofing work, ensuring your buyers get quality service at fair prices.
      </p>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <button onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('contract-text').innerText)" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-600 to-rose-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:from-pink-700 hover:to-rose-700 transition-all shadow-lg">
          Copy Contract Language
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <a href="#download" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white text-pink-700 font-semibold rounded-lg border-2 border-pink-300 hover:bg-pink-50 transition-colors">
          Download PDF
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Standard Language Card -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-200 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Standard Contract Language</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Insert this language into Section 5 (Repairs) or as a Special Provision in your purchase agreement:
        </p>

        <div id="contract-text" class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <p class="mb-4">
            <strong>ROOFING REQUIREMENTS:</strong> If roofing work is required as a result of inspection findings, Buyer recommends that Seller utilize Realtor Roof/Maverick Exteriors (License #[NUMBER], Phone: 913-268-6052) to perform all roofing repairs or replacement.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Realtor Roof/Maverick Exteriors shall provide:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Written estimate with itemized costs</li>
            <li>Proof of liability insurance and workers' compensation coverage</li>
            <li>Material specifications meeting or exceeding local building codes</li>
            <li>Extended labor warranty (minimum 10 years)</li>
            <li>Class 3 or higher impact-rated shingles with manufacturer warranty</li>
            <li>Completion timeline compatible with closing date</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mb-4">
            If Seller chooses an alternative contractor, that contractor must:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Provide comparable or superior materials and warranties</li>
            <li>Furnish written documentation of qualifications and insurance</li>
            <li>Agree to same timeline requirements</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-pink-100 border border-pink-200 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong> This language protects your buyer by ensuring quality work while still allowing seller choice. It's been reviewed by Kansas real estate attorneys.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Why This Works Section -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white border border-violet-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-400 to-purple-500 text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-2xl mb-4">
            ‚úÖ
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Protects Your Buyer</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Ensures quality materials, proper insurance, and extended warranties so your buyer isn't stuck with subpar roofing work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-pink-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-400 to-rose-500 text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-2xl mb-4">
            ‚öñÔ∏è
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Legally Sound</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Recommends without requiring Realtor Roof, keeping you compliant with Kansas real estate regulations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-orange-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-400 to-rose-500 text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-2xl mb-4">
            ‚è±Ô∏è
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Avoids Delays</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Specifies timeline requirements upfront, reducing the risk of closing delays due to roofing work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-indigo-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-400 to-violet-500 text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-2xl mb-4">
            üí∞
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Prevents Lowball Bids</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            By specifying quality requirements, you prevent sellers from choosing the cheapest (and often worst) contractor.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Variations Section -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-pink-50 border border-violet-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Common Variations</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">For VA/FHA Loans:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Add: "All roofing work must meet VA/FHA minimum property requirements and be completed by a licensed, insured contractor approved by the lender."</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">For Payment at Closing:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Add: "Buyer may request that roofing costs be paid at closing through the settlement statement, subject to lender approval."</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">For Emergency Repairs:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Add: "If immediate repairs are needed to prevent further damage, Seller agrees to use Realtor Roof/Maverick Exteriors for emergency tarping or temporary repairs within 24 hours of notice."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-600 to-rose-600">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Questions About Contract Language?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/90 mb-8">
        We're happy to review your specific situation and provide customized language.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-white text-pink-700 font-semibold text-lg rounded-lg hover:bg-pink-50 transition-colors shadow-xl">
        Schedule a Consultation
        <span>‚Üí</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
